---------------[12]
The popular meaning of anarchy as absolute chaos and disorder, what scholars call &quot;anomy&quot; (absence of order), is rejected by all the above anarchist traditions - they think that government is actually a source of disorder, and that society would be more orderly without any
The popular meaning of anarchy as absolute chaos and disorder, what some scholars call by Durkheim's sociological term &quot;anomie&quot; (absence of standards, values or order), is rejected by all the above anarchist traditions - they think that government is actually a source of disorder, and that society would be more orderly without any
