---------------[12]
These theories have radically different visions of what anarchism means: libertarian socialists intend anarchism to mean an abolition of all forms of hierarchy: political, economic, and otherwise; anarcho-capitalists envision a capitalist society with governments replaced by capitalist institutions; individualist anarchists insist above all on individual freedom from state
These theories have radically different visions of what anarchism means: libertarian socialists intend anarchism to mean the replacement of all forms of hierarchy (political, economic, and otherwise) by democratically-controled and collective-owned organizations; anarcho-capitalists envision a capitalist society with governments replaced by capitalist institutions; individualist anarchists insist above all on individual freedom from state
