Common misconception: Anarchy as Anomi
Common misconception: Anarchy as Anomie The popular meaning of anarchy as absolute chaos and disorder -- what some scholars call by Durkheim's sociological term &quot;anomie&quot; (absence of standards, values or order) -- is rejected by all the above anarchist traditions; they think that government is actually a source of disorder, and that society would be more orderly without any
