Anarcho-capitalists consider an employer-employee relationship to be an elaborate and mutually profitable form of voluntary association, and that any external power capable of preventing it is itself oppression
Anarcho-capitalists consider an employer-employee relationship to be an elaborate and mutually profitable form of voluntary association, as evidenced by the consent to a contract that each party was free to refuse, and that any external power capable of preventing such relationship is itself oppressive coercion to be fought
