---------------[12]
Also, anarchists have a history of claiming that other schools of anarchism to which they do not subscribe are not true anarchism. h&quot;It's an odd feature of the anarchist tradition over the years that it seems to have often bred highly authoritarian personality types, who legislate what the Doctrine IS, and with various degrees of fury (often great) denounce those who depart from what they have declared to be the True Principles
The following quote by Noam Chomsky demonstrates this concern: h&quot;It's an odd feature of the anarchist tradition over the years that it seems to have often bred highly authoritarian personality types, who legislate what the Doctrine IS, and with various degrees of fury (often great) denounce those who depart from what they have declared to be the True Principles
