---------------[12]
Traditional individualists do not oppose the private ownership of capital, with an important exception: Most oppose property titles to raw land, land must be in use to be rightfully possessed
Traditional individualists do not oppose the private ownership of capital, with an important exception: Most oppose property titles to land itself since it is not the product of labor and therefore oppose buying and selling of land; however, individuals may possess land by occupation or use and must remain in use to retain title to it
