---------------[12]
These philosophies use anarchy to mean a society based on voluntary interaction of free individuals
The use of anarchy to mean a society based on voluntary interaction of free individuals was first used by Louis-Armand, Baron de Lahontan in his Nouveaux voyages dans l'Amrique septentrionale where he described the indigenous american societies as being in anarchy (i.e., without government and private property)
