[[Image:Hzphotoneutral-3.jpg|thumb|right| Howard Zinn (1922-)]] Anarchism 'in General', or Generic Anarchism refers to the kind of anarchism that is most easily encountered at first glance and most often, and is represented by living figures who publicly identify themselves as anarchists, as swell as somewhat popular orgaizations and movements that exist outside of the Internet and are seen at protests or mentioned in national news media
