Tucker's economic ideas may be taken as representative; he blamed the poor condition of American workers on four state-maintained monopolies: the money monopoly: state-enforced control of currency and credit by official banks; the land monopoly: state enforcement of titles to land for owners who do not use or occupy it; patents: prohibiting competition by state-granted privilege;tariffs: restricting competition in favor of established firms
