For mutualists, this opposition does not include opposition to the product of labor or capital goods (&quot;means of production&quot;) run by individuals, but only &quot;usury&quot;, i.e. rent, interest, and profit from other's labor (profit being defined as not paying according to labor theory of value)
For mutualists, this opposition does not include opposition to the product of labor or capital goods (&quot;means of production&quot;) run by individuals, but only &quot;usury&quot;, i.e. rent, interest, and profit from other's labor (profit being defined as labor not receiving its &quot;full product&quot; under the labor theory of value)
