---------------[25]
Bernard Rimland's influential research and his book Infantile Autism (1967) which demonstrated that autism was not caused by childhood trauma or abuse, but by damage to certain areas of the brain, particularly the reticular formation which associates present sensory input with memories of past experience
Bernard Rimland's influential research and his book Infantile Autism (1967) which argued that autism was not caused by childhood trauma or abuse, but by damage to certain areas of the brain, particularly the reticular formation which associates present sensory input with memories of past experience
