Difficulty in making transitions from one situation to anothe
Indicators of this disorder include oversensitivty of underreactivity to touch, movement, sights, or sounds; physical clumsiness or carlessness; poor body awareness; a tendency to be easily distracted; impulsive physical or verbal behaviour; an activity level that is unusually high or low; the inability to unwind or calm self; difficulty learning new movements; difficulty in making transitions from one situation to another; social and/or emotional problems; delays in speech, language, or motor skills; specific learning difficulties/delays in academic achievement
