Much of this is due to the sensory system of an autistic which is quite different from the sensory system of other people, since certain stimulations can effect an autistic differently then a non-autistic, and the degree of how the sensory system is affected varies wildly from one autistic person to another
Much of this is due to the sensory system of an autistic which is quite different from the sensory system of other people, since certain stimulations can affect an autistic differently then a non-autistic, and the degree to which the sensory system is affected varies wildly from one autistic person to another
