The criteria for autism is much more controversial and some physicians today may ignore it completely, instead solely relying on other methods for determining the diagnosis. Types of autism Autism presents in a wide degree, from those who are nearly dysfunctional and apparently mentally handicapped to those whose symptoms are mild or remedied enough to appear unexceptional (&quot;normal&quot;) to the general public
