The extreme male brain theory The extreme male brain theory of autism, proposed by Simon Baron-Cohen in accordance with his empathizing-systemizing theoryTEMPLATE[ref, guardianest]TEMPLATE[ref, LawsonSystemising], suggests that autistics have extreme forms of what he describes as the male brain: they are good (often very good) at systemizing, and very bad at empathizing
