Due to the realities that Alabama is &quot;redder&quot; than just about any other Southern state and Republican voters probably number greatest in Southern suburbs, it can be said that the city of San Francisco, California and suburban Shelby County (Birmingham area) are the closest pair of greatly populated areas to being political polar opposites, especially on the cultural dimension
Alabama is one of the most conservative states in the country; Shelby County, in suburban Birmingham, and the city of San Francisco, California are the closest pair of greatly populated areas to being political polar opposites
