---------------[305]
In Greek mythology, Akhilleus Aikids (descendent of Aeacus), or plain Achilles (also transliterated as Achilleus, Akhilles, or Akhilleus) was the greatest warrior in the Trojan War, and the central character of Homer's Iliad. Birth Achilles was the son of Peleus, king of the Myrmidones in Thessaly, and the sea nymph Thetis
