---------------[307]
To achieve his main goal of preserving the Union, Lincoln decided to abolish slavery, which he did through the Emancipation Proclamation and the Thirteenth Amendment
To achieve his main goal of preserving the Union, Lincoln decided to initiate the process of abolishing slavery, which he did through his Emancipation Proclamation and his advocacy of the Thirteenth Amendment to the U.S
